---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Our Story"
	description="How a hard season, a house that wasn't forever, and repeated rainbows became the beginning of Darbees Chasing Rainbows."
>
	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24">
		<!-- Hero -->
		<div class="mb-16 text-center md:mb-20">
			<div
				class="bg-primary/10 text-primary mb-6 inline-flex h-16 w-16 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl"
			>
				<svg
					xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					class="h-8 w-8"
					viewBox="0 0 20 20"
					fill="currentColor"
				>
					<path
						fill-rule="evenodd"
						d="M3.172 5.172a4 4 0 015.656 0L10 6.343l1.172-1.171a4 4 0 115.656 5.656L10 17.657l-6.828-6.829a4 4 0 010-5.656z"
						clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
				</svg>
			</div>
			<h1 class="font-display mb-4 text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
				Our Story
			</h1>
			<p class="text-base-content/70 mx-auto max-w-2xl text-xl leading-snug md:text-2xl">
				How a hard season, a house that wasn't forever, and repeated rainbows became the beginning
				of Darbees Chasing Rainbows.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- The forever home that wasn't -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>The forever home that wasn't</h2>
			<p>In 2023, we were trying to sell the house we thought would be our forever home.</p>
			<p>
				On paper, it was 2,100 square feet — enough to sound spacious. In practice, it was designed
				for a retired couple, not a growing family. Two tiny bedrooms. A giant master suite. Not
				enough room for the life we were building. We had three children when we bought it. We soon
				had four.
			</p>
			<p>Then, layer by layer, we started discovering what the house actually was.</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Layer-by-layer problems -->
		<div class="bg-base-200 mb-16 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-6 text-2xl font-bold">What we found</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-6">We remedied what we could. But it kept going.</p>
			<ul class="text-base-content/80 space-y-3">
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span>Hidden mold</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span>Bad plumbing</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span>Poor soil — hammerhead worms and invasive Asian jumping worms</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span>Water entering a wall from an improperly installed gutter</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span>Termites, because the builders hadn't sealed them out properly</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span
						>Evidence the property had been used as a community dump decades earlier — we kept
						finding rusty saw blades and broken glass in the ground</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">—</span>
					<span
						>Mildew smell outside from overcrowded landscaping, which brought a cockroach
						infestation</span
					>
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="text-base-content mt-6 font-medium">
				We fixed what we could. But making that house into what our family needed would have taken
				more money, time, and strength than we had. So we listed it.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Living in the RV while waiting -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>Waiting in a tiny RV</h2>
			<p>We thought the house would sell quickly. It didn't.</p>
			<p>
				For months, we lived in a small RV on the property while we waited. We kept praying. We kept
				asking the Lord what He was doing. We didn't know. The path forward wasn't clear at all.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- The rainbows -->
		<div class="border-primary/20 bg-primary/5 mb-16 rounded-3xl border p-8 md:p-10">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">The rainbows</h2>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-4">
				Again and again, in moments of discouragement — when we talked about not knowing the Lord's
				will — we would see a rainbow.
			</p>
			<p class="text-base-content/80 mb-4">Not once. Not twice. Over and over.</p>
			<p class="text-base-content font-medium">
				Those rainbows became a comfort to us. A reminder that God had not forgotten our family,
				even when the path forward was unclear. The rainbow is not decoration for us. It is part of
				our testimony.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Why "Darbees" -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>Why "Darbees"</h2>
			<p>
				Darbee is our last name. The brand name "Darbees Chasing Rainbows" came directly from that
				season — a family name attached to a testimony. The "Darbees" part is simply who we are.
			</p>
			<p>
				We are not chasing comfort, perfection, or a polished life. We are chasing the reminders of
				God's faithfulness in the middle of uncertainty. We are learning to build, learn, work,
				repent, repair, and hope as we go.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- The RV is not the dream -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>The RV is not the dream</h2>
			<p>
				We have been full-time RVing ever since. We didn't set out to become forever RV people. The
				RV is the road we are walking — not the destination.
			</p>
			<p>
				It has been a training ground. It has taught us about needs versus wants, systems versus
				chaos, small-space family life, and what it feels like to be a stranger in a community over
				and over. It has given us an unreasonable view of this country and its people. It has cost
				us real things too — consistent community, friendships, belonging, and ease.
			</p>
			<p>
				We talk about all of it honestly on the <a href="/rv-life">RV Life</a> page.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Family roles and privacy -->
		<div class="mb-16">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-6 text-2xl font-bold">The family behind the site</h2>

			<div class="mb-8 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">My wife</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						She carries the daily academic load with extraordinary patience. She is the primary
						homeschool lead — adapting to each child's needs, keeping the core work moving, and
						knowing when to push, when to slow down, and when the whole day needs mercy.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-base-300 rounded-2xl border p-6">
					<div class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold">Me</div>
					<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
						I document the journey, build the systems, write the posts, and bring the side roads:
						theology, art, music, economics, tracking, taxonomy, herbal knowledge, nature
						identification, and practical projects. I also work full-time as a senior software
						engineer.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-base-200 rounded-2xl p-6">
				<div class="mb-2 font-semibold">Our four kids</div>
				<p class="text-base-content/80 text-sm">
					We have four children. They are part of everything on this site, but they are not the
					product. You may see their projects, hikes, drawings, notebooks, hands, and the life we
					are building together — but we protect their faces and their private moments.
				</p>
				<p class="text-base-content mt-3 text-sm font-medium">
					We share family life, but we do not make our children the product.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Kingdom Farm -->
		<div class="prose prose-lg mb-16 max-w-none">
			<h2>Kingdom Farm</h2>
			<p>
				Kingdom Farm is the next major destination — but not the final one. It is a long-term vision
				for regenerative food, faithful work, practical mercy, hospitality, and deeper roots. We are
				scouting land, studying regenerative farming, counting the cost, and building toward it
				honestly.
			</p>
			<p>
				The deeper goal is larger than a farm: to become the kind of family that can build, steward,
				serve, and endure faithfully wherever the Lord leads.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a href="/kingdom-farm">Read more about Kingdom Farm →</a>
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- How We Share -->
		<div class="bg-base-200 mb-16 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10">
			<h2 class="font-display mb-6 text-2xl font-bold">How we share</h2>
			<ul class="text-base-content/80 space-y-3">
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We tell the truth, but not everything.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We protect our children — no faces, no private or embarrassing moments.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We share enough to be useful, not enough to make our family the product.</span>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span
						>No display ads. Affiliate links are disclosed and limited to things we actually use.</span
					>
				</li>
				<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
					<span class="text-primary mt-1 shrink-0">→</span>
					<span>We correct mistakes publicly when we get things wrong.</span>
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="text-base-content/60 mt-6 text-sm">
				<a href="/support" class="hover:text-primary underline transition-colors"
					>How This Site Is Supported →</a
				>
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Closing invitation -->
		<div class="border-base-300 border-t pt-12 text-center">
			<p class="text-base-content/70 mx-auto mb-8 max-w-md">
				If any of this resonates, you're welcome here. We're glad you found us.
			</p>
			<div class="mb-10 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
				<a href="/start-here" class="btn btn-primary">Start Here</a>
				<a href="/kingdom-farm" class="btn btn-outline">Follow Kingdom Farm</a>
				<a href="/homeschool" class="btn btn-ghost">Our Homeschool</a>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div id="newsletter" class="border-base-300 mt-4 border-t pt-12">
			<NewsletterSignup />
		</div>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
